{{Infobox language |name=Andaqui |nativename=Jirara|states=[[Colombia]] |region=southern highlands |ethnicity=[[Andaqui people]] |extinct=? |ref=e08 |familycolor=American |family=[[Paezan languages|Paezan]] or [[Barbacoan languages|Barbacoan]] ? |iso3=ana |glotto=anda1286 |glottorefname=Andaqui }}
'''Andaqui''' (or '''Andaki''') is an extinct language from the southern highlands of [[Colombia]]. It has been linked to the [[Paezan languages|Paezan]] or [[Barbacoan languages]], but no connections have been demonstrated. It was spoken by the [[Andaqui people]] of [[Colombia]].
