{{Infobox language |name=Aruáshi |nativename=Aruá |region=[[Brazil]] |speakers=12 |date=1990 |ref = e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Tupian languages|Tupian]] |fam2=[[Monde languages|Monde]] |iso3=arx |glotto=arua1261 |glottorefname=Arua (Rodonia State) }}
'''Aruáshi''', or '''Aruá''', is a nearly extinct [[Tupian languages|Tupian language]] of the states of [[Rondônia]] and [[Mato Grosso]], in the [[Amazon region]] of [[Brazil]]. There were 131 Aruá in 2012 and about 20 people who speak Aruá as a maternal language.
