{{Infobox language |name=Humahuaca |nativename=Omaguaca |states=[[Argentina]] |ethnicity = |extinct=? |familycolor=American |family=unclassified |iso3=none |linglist=1nm |glotto=none }} '''Humahuaca''' (Omaguaca) is an extinct and unclassified language of [[Argentina]] (Campbell & Grondona 2012). Tribal and possibly dialect divisions were Fiscara, Jujuy, Ocloya, Osa, Purmamarca, and Tiliar. Mason (1950) proposed that Humahuaca was related to [[Diaguita language|Diaguita]] (Cacán) and [[Kunza language|Kunza]] in a group he called "Ataguitan", but modern sources leave it unclassified due to a lack of data.
