'''Jayadevi tai Ligade''' is an Indian writer in the [[Kannada]] language.<ref>{{cite book |last= Shankaragouda Hanmantagouda Patil|title= Community Dominance and Political Modernisation: The Lingayats
|url=     https://books.google.co.in/books?id=R84n-Wv1S-8C&pg=PA306&lpg=PA306&ots=gkldor5A3j&focus=viewport&dq=Solapur+Kannada+Association&output=html_text |date = April 2002 |location= [[Karnataka]], [[India]] |publisher= Mittal Publications|page=306 |isbn= 9788170998679|access-date= April 2015}}</ref> She became the president of [[Kannada Sahitya Parishat]]tu. She fought to unify [[Sholapur]] with [[Karnataka]] on the linguistic grounds of majority Kannada-speaking community in the city.<ref>{{cite book|last=Patil|first=Shankaragouda Hanamantagouda|title=Community Dominance and Political Modernisation: The Lingayats|year=2002|publisher=Mittal Publications|isbn=8170998670|pages=45, 306|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=R84n-Wv1S-8C&lpg=PA45&ots=gjm8tqaA0m&dq=Jayadevi%20tai%20Ligade&pg=PA45#v=onepage&q=Jayadevi%20tai%20Ligade&f=false}}</ref> She has published several books on sharana sahitya in Kannada and Marathi, and wrote [[Siddheshwar|Siddarama]] [[Puranas|purana]], ''Sri Siddarameshwara''.<ref>[http://lingayatreligion.com/Sharanaru/Siddarameswara.htm Lingayat Religion- Siddarameswara<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=KnPoYxrRfc0C&lpg=PA4392&ots=Y6JzG1mDvY&dq=Jayadevi%20Thaayi%20Ligade&pg=PA4394#v=onepage&q=Jayadevi%20Thaayi%20Ligade&f=false The Encyclopaedia Of Indian Literature (Volume Five (Sasay To Zorgot) - Mohan Lal - Google Boeken<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  She also helped by paying some donation in inventing and publishing sharana sahitya.<ref>[http://www.hindu.com/2004/01/30/stories/2004013003820300.htm Hindu.com] retrieved 3rd Jan 2010</ref>

